ft><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br>  Posts: 2923<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/15/02 9:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wow, using a bolt DOES take skill!</span><hr size=1> Bolts no longer double hit.<br>
<br>
And yes I could bug this, but actually... I am fairly certian that the problem is one of two things.<br>
<br>
1.  Somehow the wall geometry calculations for LoS do not match what is actually seen by the player.  In order to fix the &quot;bug&quot; they'd have to go through and determine every situation where this could happen, which I believe would be a literal impossibility.  You see how he's standing close to the corner?  That's probably it.  The point of that corner is probably treated as being in the same place as the mob.  The thing is, in this exact same &quot;apparent&quot; situation, a bolt might land 9 other times with no issue.<br>
<br>
2.  The skeleton model screwed things up.<br>
<br>
<br>
The point is, this sort of thing happens all the time, despite what mages might arrogantly claim.  I actually have another screenshot from this same group of a clear shot that missed.  I only loaded one to save space.  <br>
<br>
It <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">is</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> true that for every situation where a bolt unexpectedly misses, you can have one where the bolt unexpectedly hits.  So what this is saying is that mages bragging about their &quot;skill&quot; are probably either lying through their teeth or hunt in the exact same spot every single day.  <br>
