<br>
I believe this is Goladus's attempt to convince wizards that Firebolt of Tallon is useless and wizards shouldn't pay it any attention during class balancing conversations.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh dear I blew all my mana for zero damage because bolts are so difficult to use.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes it's frustrating that we can't use bolts near walls and it'll be a wonderful day if/when Sony programmers would fix it.  But until then use AE rains and direct damage spells when mobs are near walls.<br>
<br>
Tell your group to keep the mobs in the center of the room.  Ask shamans to shrink everybody and to cast Grow on you so your bolts go over their head.  Ask an enchanter to cast ogre on you and gnome on everyone else.<br>
<br>
And those skeletons are wearing clogs not slippers. <p><a target="Amel Rathanon" href="http://www.familjenguild.com/dspMember.php?Name=Amel">Sage Amel Rathanon {Arch Convoker}</a><br>
